// Regression: minimal program preamble must compile with gcc -ffreestanding.
// Before fix: emitter unconditionally emitted `_zer_mtx_ensure_init_cv`
// referencing pthread types, but <pthread.h> was gated on __STDC_HOSTED__.
// Result: every program (even empty) failed to compile bare-metal —
// 'PTHREAD_MUTEX_RECURSIVE' undeclared in preamble.
// Fix: wrap mutex helpers in the same __STDC_HOSTED__ guard as the
// barrier/semaphore helpers.
//
// This test only verifies the program compiles + runs on hosted (the
// usual test path). The actual freestanding-compile check is documented
// in BUGS-FIXED.md and manually verified with `gcc -ffreestanding`.

u32 main() {
    return 0;
}
